&#xa0;
[normal]Written evidence submitted[bold] by the Marine Reserves Coalition[bold]This submission is supported by the following Marine Reserves Coalition members:
[normal]Executive summary[bold]The Marine Reserves Coalition 
[normal]recommends that:
[normal]Introduction[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The plans for implementing the 27 so far approved MCZs.[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]How those MCZs will be monitored, managed and enforced, and the needs of different stakeholders — including fishing, leisure and extractive industries — will be balanced against environment protection.[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The plans to improve the evidence base for considering potential further Zones, including the priorities and funding of the research bodies that will undertake the necessary research.[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]What the balance of factors should be — social and economic factors, as well as environmental factors — in considering further potential MCZs.[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]The level of ambition in the programme to establish protected areas (including MCZs), compared with the need for biodiversity protection.[bold]&#xa0;
